  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis model includes tunable configuration parameters — base mesh edge length, power-law damage exponent threshold, and turbulent viscosity ratio cap — whose values were selected during validation but are not pinned in a settings node or constrained by the COU. Validation results are reported at the chosen settings without binding those settings to deployment.",
