      "name": "Bench-scale hemolysis validation against FDA GCBP experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA GCBP experimental measurements across 5 flow-speed operating points. At the chosen settings (base mesh edge length 0.15 mm, power-law damage exponent threshold 0.42, turbulent viscosity ratio cap 100), mean NIH error was 8.3% with all points within 15% of experimental values. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all operating points. No configuration settings node is linked; deployment teams are expected to reproduce these settings from the narrative description alone.",
      "quantitativeResult": "Mean NIH prediction error 8.3%; maximum 14.7%; RH < 1 at all 5 operating points.",
