      "description": "Three mesh refinement levels evaluated. The intermediate mesh (base edge length 0.15 mm, approximately 4.2 million cells) was selected as the deployment mesh based on a Richardson extrapolation GCI of 2.1%. Coarser and finer meshes showed GCI values of 7.8% and 0.9% respectively. The selected mesh size is documented in the validation narrative but is not enforced via a pinned configuration record; the turbulent viscosity ratio cap and damage exponent threshold were held at their chosen values throughout but remain undeclared in any machine-readable settings artifact.",
      "quantitativeResult": "GCI at selected mesh: 2.1%; discretization uncertainty within acceptable bounds for MRL 2.",
      "validationStatus": "passed"
